Solving recurrence relation
1.	 An = an-1 +2          a0 = 1
2.	 An = an-1 + n          a0 = 4
3.	  An = 3an-1 +2        a0  = 1

1.	 An = an-1 +2          a0 = 1

 An = an-1 +2      ------- (1)       n=1  
An = an-k +2*k--------- (1.1)    k=1     
An-1 = an-2 +2
       An = an-2 +2+2= an-2 +4--------- (2)
      An = an-k +2*k--------------- (2.1)     k=2,n=2
      An-2 = an-3+2
      An=an-3+2+4= an-3+6-----------(3)
      An=an-k+2*k--------------- (3.1)        k=3,n=3
     K=0,1,2,3,4,5,6,7,………..,n
    An=an-k+2*k                    let take(n=k)
A0=a0+2*0;
A0=a0--1
   An=an-n+2*n
   A0=a0+2*n
  A0 = 1+2n-------- Generalize equation
 A0 = 1n^0+2n^1
Time complexity ------ O(n)
 
2.	an = an-1 + n          a0 = 4----(1)
an = an-k +k n          
  an-1=an-2+n-------- (2)
an=an-2+n+n
an=an-2+2n---------- (3)
an=an-k+kn
an-2 = an-3+n----------(4)

an = an-3+n+2n
an = an-3+3n--------------(5)
an = an-k+kn

k=0,1,2,3,4,5……,n

an = an-k+kn                let assume (n=k)

an = an-n+n*n  
an = a0+n*n  
an=4+n2      
time complexity    O(n2)                      


3.	An = 3an-1 +2        a0  = 1------ (1)
An=3kan-k+3k-1           k=1
An-1=3(an-2)+2

An=3(3an-2+2)+2
An=9an-2+6+2
An=9an-2+8             ---------(2)
An=3kan-k+3k-1                k=2
An-2=3an-3+2
An=9(3an-3+2)+8
An=27an-3+18+8
An=27an-3+26--------------(3)
An=3kan-k+3k-1     k=3           
K=0,1,2,3,4,5,6,7,………….,n

Generalize
An=3kan-k+3k-1                (n=k)        
An=3nan-n+3n-1 
An=3na0+3n-1       
An=3n+3n-1     
An=(2*3n)-1  


Time complexity
O(3n)              

4.	An=7an-1-10an-2    a0=2 and a1=3  
5.	 An=6n-1-9an-2        a0=1 and a1=4
             



An=7an-1-10an-2    a0=2 and a1=3  
 The characteristic equation
An-7an-1+10an-2 =0 -> (1)
X2 – 7X+10=10

Quadratic equation 
( -b +-sqrt(b2-4ac))/ 2a

A=1;
B=-7;
C=10
7+-(sqrt(49-40)/2
7+-(sqrt(9))/2
(7+-3)/2
10/2=5-----root 1
4/2=2------- root 2
An= 5a+2b
An= a*5n+ b*2n

N=0
A0 =a*50+ b*20
2=a+b  ---- 1)
N=1
A1= a*51+ b*21
3=a*5+b*2----- 2)

  2A+2b=4
5a+2b=3
-3a=1
A=-1/3
A+b=2
-1/3+b=2
B=2+1/3
B=6+1/3
B=7/3
An= -1/3*5n+ 7/3*2n
Time complexity---- O(2n)

 An=6n-1-9an-2        a0=1 and a1=4
Char eqn
An-6n-1+9n-2=0
X2- 6X+9=0
A=1;
B=-6
C=9

Quadratic equation 
( -b +-sqrt(b2-4ac))/ 2a
6+-sqrt(36-36)/2
6/2=3
3 ---- root 1
An=a*3n+b*3n*n
A1=a*31+b*31*1
4=3a+3b;
4=3+3b
3b=1
B=1/3;
A0=a*30+b*30*0
1=a
An=1*3n+b*(1/3)n*n
Time complexity
O(3n)

1.	T(n)=T(n/2)+1     T(1) =1
2.	T(n)=T(n/2)+n   T(1)=1
3.	T(n)=2T(n/2)+n   T(1)  =1


T(n/1)=T(n/2^1)+1
T(n/2)= T(n/2^2)+1
T(n)=T(n/2^2)+2
T(n/2^2)=T(n/2^3)+1
T(n)= T(n/2^3)+3

T(n)=T(n/2k) +k

n/2k=1
n=2k
k=log2(n)
T(n)=T(n/n)+ log2(n)

T(n)=1+ log2(n)
Time complexity -- log2(n)

T(n)=T(n/2)+n   T(1)=1
T(n/2) = T(n/22) +n/2
T(n)= T(n/22) +n/2+n  
T(n/22)= T(n/23)+n/22
T(n)= T(n/23)+n/22+n/2+n  
T(n)= T(n/23)+n(1/22+1/2+1)  

T(n)= T(n/23)+n(1+1)
T(n)= T(n/23) +2n
T(n)= T(n/2k) +2n
n/2k=1
n=2k
k=log2(n)

T(n)= T(n/n) +2n
T(n)=1+2n

Time complexity is O(n) 
1.	T(n)=2T(n/2)+n   T(1)  =1
T(n/2)=2T(n/22) +n/2

T(n)=2(2T(n/22) +n/2) +n   
T(n)=4T(n/22) +n +n   
T(n)= 4T(n/22) +2n
T(n/22)=2t(n/23) +n/22

T(n)= 8t(n/23) +n+2n
T(n)= 8t(n/23) +3n
T(n)= 2kT(n/2k) +kn
n/2k=1
n=2k
k=log2(n)
T(n)= nT(n/n)+n log2(n)
T(n)= n+n log2(n)
Time complexity - n log2(n)
O(1) ; O(n); O(n2); O(2n); log2(n) ;   n log2(n)






 





Void fun(int num)  
T(n-1)+n+1--T(n-1)+n      T(1)=1
{
If(num==1)// 1 unit of time
Break;
Else
Printf(“%d”,n);  n unit 
Fun(num-1);  T(n-1)

}




































